<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-11T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-11T14:00:00-05:00" n="283" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">840.6362/3–1147: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gallman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-11T19:00:00+00:00">March
                                        11, 1947—7 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1566. This is <gloss target="#t_Salco1">Salco</gloss> 445.
                                Possibility of UK seeking import US coal still receiving Cabinet
                                consideration. However, we do not anticipate <pb facs="0512" n="494" xml:id="pg_494"/> reversal previous decision unless dollar
                                shortages other <gloss target="#t_ECO1">ECO</gloss> countries
                                prevent them from taking all US availability. In that case, possible
                                UK may buy surplus for purpose building stocks.<note n="1" xml:id="d283fn1">Chargé Gallman in telegram 1648 (<gloss target="#t_Salco1">Salco</gloss> 451), March 14, from
                                    London, reported: “British Cabinet decided today request <gloss target="#t_ECO1">ECO</gloss> for allocation US coal to UK.”
                                    (840.6362/3–1447)</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gallman</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>